{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/"},{"type":"text","text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pmtiles:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"asset:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load an asset or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"file:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a local PMTiles file."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"PMTiles sources currently do not support caching or offline pack downloads."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile server."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"pmtiles-demo.png"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift